Notes that matter for correctness/performance
Deterministic varList ordering

In C++ above I used sorted key order for jsonBlock keys because nlohmann::json iterates object keys in sorted order by default. This matches typical existing C++ behavior and prevents mismatch with how varList[i] maps to keys.

If your existing C++ uses nlohmann::ordered_json (insertion order), tell me and I’ll adjust the selection helper to use insertion order instead; then your Python UI should keep insertion order too (it already does).

Remaining bottleneck

After removing file IO, the next big cost for huge sweeps is ProcessPoolExecutor overhead per combination. If combinations explode, the best next step is chunking (each worker evaluates many varLists per call). I can give a chunked version too, but the above is the minimal “no file IO” change you asked for.









